post.description:
This endpoint allows you to check the availability of an Freight LTL pickup service. The pickup availability depends on two factors, the cut off time and the access time.

**Cut off time** - The latest time allowed for a pickup to be scheduled. The time is local to the pickup postal code.

**Access time** - The time between the pickup ready time (when the package is ready to be picked) and the time when the driver is ready to pick up the package.

Note: FedEx APIs do not support Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) mechanism.

FullSchema.description: The request elements for requesting a freight rate quote.

value.description:
This is the account number. Maximum Length is 9.
Example: XXX456XXX

LTLRootAccountNumber.description:
This is the Account number details.
Note:
  • In case if this is shipping account number, do use the account number used for creating Auth Token.

returnTransitTimes.description: Indicate if the transit time and commit data are to be returned in the reply. Default value is false.

servicesNeededOnRateFailure.description: Specify the services to be requested if the rate data is not available.

variableOptions.description: Specify service options whose combinations are to be considered when replying with available services.

rateSortOrder.description:
This is a sort order you can specify to control the order of the response data:
Example:
  • SERVICENAMETRADITIONAL - data in order of highest to lowest service (Default)
  • COMMITASCENDING - data in order of ascending delivery committment
  • COMMITDESCENDING - data in order of descending delivery committment.

LTLRateRequestControlParameters.description: These are various parameters you can provide for filtering and sorting  capability in the response, such as transit time and commit data, rate sort order etc.

shipper.description: The descriptive data for the physical location from which the shipment originates.

serviceType.description: The FedEx service type for the shipment. The results will be filtered by the serviceType value indicated.  If no serviceType is indicated then all the applicable services and corresponding rates will be returned.Allowed service types are FEDEX_FREIGHT_PRIORITY and FEDEX_FREIGHT_ECONOMY.

preferredCurrency.description:
Indicates the currency the caller requests to have used in all returned monetary values (when a choice is possible). Used in conjunction with the rateRequestType data element.
Example: USD
Click here to see Currency Codes

rateRequestType.description:
Indicate the type of rates to be returned. The account specific rates are returned by default if the account number is specified in the request.
Following are values:
  • LIST - Returns FedEx published list rates in addition to account-specific rates (if applicable).
  • INCENTIVE - This is one-time discount for incentivising the customer. For more information, contact your FedEx representative.
  • ACCOUNT - Returns account specific rates (Default).
Examples: ["INCENTIVE", "LIST"]

shipDateStamp.description:
This is the Shipment date. Required for future ship date rates.Default is current date if not indicated or date is in the past.
The format is YYYY-MM-DD
Example: 2019-09-06

requestedPackageLineItems.description:
One or more package-attribute descriptions, each of which describes an individual package, a group of identical packages, or (for the total-piece-total-weight case) common characteristics of all packages in the shipment.
At least one array instance containing the weight for at least one package is required for freight shipments.
Single piece requests will have one RequestedPackageLineItem.
Multiple piece requests will have multiple RequestedPackageLineItems.
Maximum occurrences is 99.

totalPackageCount.description:
Conditional
Indicates the total number of packages in the shipment.
The Maximum number of packages in a rate request is 100.

totalWeight.description:
Conditional. Identifies the total weight of the shipment being conveyed to FedEx.
  This is only applicable to International shipments and should be used on the first package of a multiple piece shipment. This value contains 1 explicit decimal position.

LTLRequestedShipment.description: This contains shipment data describing the shipment for which a  freight rate quote (or rate-shopping comparison) is desired.

LTLPayment.description: These are details about shipment payment.

responsibleParty.description: These are payer details such as address, account and contacts.

LTLPayor.description: This is payer Information responsible for paying for the shipment.

accountNumber.value:
This is the account number. Maximum Length is 9.
Example: Your account number

value.description:
Specify value of the account number. Maximum length is 9.
Example: XXXXX6789

AccountNumber.description:
This is the Account number details.
Note:
  • If the paymentType is Sender, then the account number is optional in shippingChargesPayment.
  • In case if this is shipping account number, do use the account number used for creating Auth Token.

subPackagingType.description:
This is a physical packaging type used for the package.
Example: TUBE, CARTON, CONTAINER. etc.
Click here to see Sub-Packaging Types
For more information on physical packaging or packaging regulatory requirements, visit FedEx.com or contact your FedEx representative.
Note: Sub packaging CAGE is not applicable for LTL Freight shipment.

groupPackageCount.description:
Indicate the grouped package count. These are number of identical package(s) each with one or more commodities.
Example: 2
